The '''shocker''', also known [[colloquialism|colloquially]] as "two in the pink, one in the stink,"<ref name="dailycal">{{Cite news|url=http://archive.dailycal.org/article/22706/sex_on_tuesday_not-so-shocking_news|title=Not-So-Shocking News|last=Borden|first=Christine|date=2007-01-23|work=|newspaper=[[The Daily Californian]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131022042259/http://archive.dailycal.org/article.php?id=22706|archive-date=2013-10-22|dead-url=yes|access-date=2016-08-18|via=}}</ref><ref name="McKinnis">{{cite web|url=http://www.vita.mn/story.php?id=17243159|title= advice – alexis on the sexes – Shock and ow – The shocking truth about a much-hyped sexual gesture. |last=McKinnis|first=Alexis|date=April 3, 2008 |work=Edition: METRO, Section: VITA.MN|publisher=Star Tribune: Newspaper of the Twin Cities (Minneapolis, MN) |pages=35 |id=Record Number: 080403alexis0403vita |accessdate=2011-02-16}}</ref> is a [[hand gesture]] with a sexual connotation.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Mauney|first1=Matt|title=Disney digitally alters 'crude' hand gesture in Rock 'n' Roller Coaster|url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/travel/attractions/the-daily-disney/os-disney-rock-n-roller-steven-tyler-gesture-story.html|accessdate=19 August 2016|publisher=[[Orlando Sentinel]]}}</ref> The [[ring finger]] and [[thumb]] are curled or bent down while the other fingers are extended. The index and middle fingers are kept together (touching) and the back of the hand faces outwards (away from the gesturer). The gesture refers to [[Fingering (sexual act)|the act]] of inserting the [[index finger|index]] and [[middle finger]]s into a [[vagina]] and the little finger into the recipient's [[anus]], hence the "shock".

